1. Linearity of Expectation (Slicing Time)Concept: 
Break the expected sum of k messy, dependent steps into individual, independent slices.
Rule: E[Total] = sum{i=1 to k} E[X_i].
2. Expected Value of a Uniform DrawConcept: 
When you pick exactly 1 item randomly from a pool of N items, its expected value is just the mathematical average of the entire pool.
Rule: E[Pick] = Total Pool Sum/N.
3. Linear State TransitionsConcept: 
If the probability of changing your state remains constant (like a fixed m/N chance), 
the expected value of your next state increases by a fixed constant.
Rule: E[Next State] = Current State + Constant.
